<emphasis id="26A2EAD8FFD53E6F1B8CFAD0FF36FAD4" box="[154,210,1349,1372]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">Note.</emphasis>
– 
<location id="11096011FFD53E6F1BFAFAD0FEF0FAD5" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:9C7F87DCFFD43E6F182DFD0FFAB1F8FE:11096011FFD53E6F1BFAFAD0FEF0FAD5" box="[236,276,1349,1373]" country="Iran" county="Haussknecht" municipality="Among" name="The" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">The</location>
protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="D3D64D49FFD53E6F1AA0FAD0FDE0FAD4" box="[438,516,1349,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Scrophularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="26A2EAD8FFD53E6F1AA0FAD0FDE0FAD4" box="[438,516,1349,1372]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">S. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provides the following indications: “Verbr.: Südwestliches 
<collectingCountry id="6CC1765AFFD53E6F1AE8FAF0FDAAFAF5" box="[510,590,1381,1405]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">Persien</collectingCountry>
: Kalkfelsen bei Persepolis und Kotel Parrou, 5000’ (leg. 
<collectorName id="B923531CFFD53E6F1909FA10FD67FA15" box="[543,643,1413,1437]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">Hausskn.</collectorName>
<date id="6068100AFFD53E6F199FFA10FD1AFA15" box="[649,766,1413,1437]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" value="1868-04">
<collectingDate id="702CE9E2FFD53E6F199FFA10FD1AFA15" box="[649,766,1413,1437]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" value="1868-04">April 1868</collectingDate>
</date>
sub 
<taxonomicName id="D3D64D49FFD53E6F1BB7FA30FEBCFA35" authority="Boiss." authorityName="Boiss." box="[161,344,1445,1469]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Scrophularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="farinosa">
<emphasis id="26A2EAD8FFD53E6F1BB7FA30FEEAFA35" box="[161,270,1445,1469]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">S. farinosa</emphasis>
Boiss.
</taxonomicName>
)”. 
<location id="11096011FFD53E6F1A63FA30FE33FA34" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:9C7F87DCFFD43E6F182DFD0FFAB1F8FE:11096011FFD53E6F1A63FA30FE33FA34" box="[373,471,1445,1468]" country="Iran" county="Haussknecht" municipality="Among" name="However" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">However</location>
, there is no mention of the herbarium of deposition of the type and lectotypification is needed. 
<collectingMunicipality id="F40DACB0FFD53E6F1BD9FA70FEC6FA75" box="[207,290,1509,1533]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">Among</collectingMunicipality>
herbaria where corresponding material has been traced, herbarium JE, where the 
<collectingCounty id="FD084E46FFD53E6F1916F990FD6EF995" box="[512,650,1541,1565]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">Haussknecht</collectingCounty>
herbarium is now incorporated, has 
<specimenCount id="02D0FD43FFD53E6F1A69F9B0FDFFF9B5" box="[383,539,1573,1597]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
by 
<collectorName id="B923531CFFD53E6F1954F9B0FD29F9B5" box="[578,717,1573,1597]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">Haussknecht</collectorName>
that were recently databased as 
<typeStatus id="CB6D8868FFD53E6F1A82F9D0FE15F9D5" box="[404,497,1605,1629]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">syntypes</typeStatus>
. Both have an identification label by Stiefelhagen as “ 
<taxonomicName id="D3D64D49FFD53E6F1AA3F9F0FD1AF9F5" authority="Stiefelhagen" authorityName="Stiefelhagen" authorityYear="2016" box="[437,766,1637,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Scrophularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nana" status="nov. spec.">
<emphasis id="26A2EAD8FFD53E6F1AA3F9F0FD95F9F4" box="[437,625,1637,1661]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">Scrophularia nana</emphasis>
Stiefelhagen
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3D9157A3FFD53E6F1B62F910FF38F914" box="[116,220,1669,1692]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" rank="species">nov. spec.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; det. 
<determinerName id="E1B5DA0EFFD53E6F1A05F910FE0CF915" box="[275,488,1669,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">Heinz Stiefelhagen.</determinerName>
1909”. However, only one of them [JE00010886] has a locality (“In rup. calc. ca. Persepolis et Kotel Parrou; 5000”) that matches the protologue. Consequently, this specimen has been selected as 
<typeStatus id="CB6D8868FFD53E6F1980F970FD1FF975" box="[662,763,1765,1789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The second specimen, [JE00010885], with locality “In rup. calc. ca. Persepolis et Kotel Kumaredj”, is not cited in the diagnosis and despite its label by Stiefelhagen, it should not be considered as type material. Duplicates of these collections in other herbaria have either a locality with elements of these two collections [G00330575] or a locality which is too vague to be attributed to one of these collections [W0017409]. Both should be considered as probable isolectotypes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="146936CAFFD53E6F185CFA30FB6DF915" blockId="7.[804,1455,1348,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">
In the diagnosis of this species a wide variation of leaf shape is mentioned. Among all observed specimens, margin leaf is irregular crenate, serrate to dentate or incised, but never pinnatipartite. This character is very important and a distinguishing trait between 
<taxonomicName id="D3D64D49FFD53E6F1F03F9B0FB86F9B4" authorityName="Stiefelhagen" authorityYear="2016" box="[1045,1122,1573,1596]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Scrophularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="26A2EAD8FFD53E6F1F03F9B0FB86F9B4" box="[1045,1122,1573,1596]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">S. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D3D64D49FFD53E6F1F82F9B0FAEFF9B5" box="[1172,1291,1573,1597]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Scrophularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longiflora">
<emphasis id="26A2EAD8FFD53E6F1F82F9B0FAEFF9B5" box="[1172,1291,1573,1597]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="202">S. longiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Another point is that the fruit of this species was not described. Based on examined specimens and digital images, we provide above a description of capsules and seeds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
